metadata.transcript: My name is Minseok Kim.  Yes, it's spelt out as M-I-N.  S-E-O-K CA UD  I think I like my name. My grandfather gave it to me. There were some candidates for my name, but one of them was same as previous president of Korea. So my grandfather disagreed. So he said Min-suk is better than the other one. So he gave me this name. Are you working or are you a student? I'm a student in Australia studying in university, majoring in marketing.  Ah, yeah. For the course itself, I like it, but sometimes I meet some strange professors or lecturers, but I do enjoy my major.  When I have free time,  I have my own YouTube channel. So I film with my friend or so after that I edit those videos and upload it on YouTube.  And for daily hobbies, I go to gym to work out.  My hometown is called Daegu. It's located at the southern part of Korea, Korean Peninsula.
